Core concepts and fundamental issues of philosophy and ethics. Different conceptions of science. The position of nursing science in the classification of sciences. The impact of different philosophical approaches on the development of nursing science. Objectives of nursing science and nursing science research, and relations between nursing science and nursing practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To deepen the knowledge of nursing science and its philosophical and ethical fundamentals. To deepen the knowledge of the objectives of nursing science research, principal issues and trends of nursing science. To develop an understanding of the impact of philosophical viewpoints on the development of nursing science knowledge, nursing practice, nursing management, nursing education and research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course: - understands the philosophical and ethical issues of nursing science and knows the relevant core concepts; - is able to explain the impact of different philosophical approaches on the development of nursing science and evidence-based practice; - knows and understands the objectives and trends of nursing science and nursing science research.
